    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect errno usage in thread creation and synchronization functions\n\n### Summary\nThe OpenAirInterface 5G codebase contained incorrect errno usage patterns in several pthread-related functions. The bug manifested as incorrect error codes being reported when pthread operations failed, particularly under high system load or resource contention scenarios.\n\nThe issue was that errno was being accessed directly in AssertFatal calls, but intervening function calls within the AssertFatal macro (such as fprintf) could modify errno before it was actually used in the format string. This led to misleading error reports that made debugging thread creation failures extremely difficult.\n\nThe problem was particularly evident in functions that create and manage the process_stats_thread, where error reports would show unrelated errno values instead of the actual pthread failure codes.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/system.c`: Fixed errno handling in threadCreate, has_cap_sys_nice, and lock_memory_to_ram functions by saving errno immediately after pthread function failures before calling AssertFatal or logging functions.\n\n"
}